path.id: I walk in that line between systems and stories, a place where science meets intuition, code brushes against the unseen I am a software developer who enjoys studying how things work - not just in the physical world, but also in those spaces between ideas, symbols, and lived experience My interests lie in science, art, applied machine learning, and video game development To me, these are not separate pursuits, but different ways of observing the same mystery: how patterns are formed, how meaning emerges, and how stories come into being I build things slowly and deliberately Sometimes tools, other times small worlds, at times experiments asking more questions than they answer I think curiosity is a form of devotion: a gentle practice of looking deeper, without rushing to close the unknown If my work has a theme, it is this: to investigate the in-between, give quiet form to intuition, and create spaces â€” digital or otherwise â€” where others might pause, notice something subtle, and feel the same spark that moves me
